Sentencas: The effect of introducing 1-3 wt % copper oxide sintering additive on the electrical and electrochemical characteristics of promising anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta was studied.
Titulo: Effect of the Copper Oxide Sintering Additive on the Electrical and Electrochemical Properties of Anode Materials Based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: The total conductivity increases with increasing amount of copper oxide.
Titulo: Effect of the Copper Oxide Sintering Additive on the Electrical and Electrochemical Properties of Anode Materials Based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: The maximum conductivity in humid hydrogen at 800A degrees C, 45 S cm(-1), was reached on introducing 3 wt % CuO.
Titulo: Effect of the Copper Oxide Sintering Additive on the Electrical and Electrochemical Properties of Anode Materials Based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: The sintering additive enhances the electrochemical activity of Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta and Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 anodes.
Titulo: Effect of the Copper Oxide Sintering Additive on the Electrical and Electrochemical Properties of Anode Materials Based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: A decrease in the sintering temperature of the anodes containing CuO with the electrolyte based on lanthanum gallate directly correlates with the electrochemical activity of the anodes.
Titulo: Effect of the Copper Oxide Sintering Additive on the Electrical and Electrochemical Properties of Anode Materials Based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: The minimum value of the polarization resistivity, 0.15 Omega cm(2) at 800A degrees D in a humid hydrogen atmosphere, was obtained for the composite anode with 3 wt % CuO sintered at a temperature of 1050 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of the Copper Oxide Sintering Additive on the Electrical and Electrochemical Properties of Anode Materials Based on Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ
